    <field name="scopecontent_teim">This subseries spans Scoppetta's years in the administrations of Mayors Beame and Lindsay in his capacity as Commissioner of Investigation for the City of New York (1972–1977) and Deputy Mayor for Criminal Justice (1976–1978). It includes a significant amount of material on NYPD Detective Robert "Bob" Leuci's cooperation with the Knapp Commission's investigations into police and criminal justice system corruption (Box 1, Folders 11-16). Leuci's involvement inspired former NYPD Commissioner Robert Daley to write Prince of the City: The True Story of a Cop Who Knew Too Much (1978), which was later filmed by director Sidney Lumet.</field>
